        dc:description           "FIG. 10. — Lithophylax trigeri A. Milne-Edwards & Brocchi, 1879, ventral side and male gonopods: A, ventral side, restored from many specimens, semi-diagrammatic reconstruction (left half: male; right half: female; bold dash line: extension of abdomen before clearing); B, C, MHN LM 2005.1.6; B, dorsal view, posterior part of cephalothorax cleared (the arrow indicates G2); C, ventral view, abdomen partly cleared (the arrow indicates G1). Abbreviations: b, basophthalmite; b.p., button of the press-button; d, depressions; e, exopodite of mxp3; e.c., episternal cupules; G1, G2, male gonopods 1 and 2; md, mandible; r, rostrum; v, vulva; 1-7, sternites 1-7. Scale bars: 2 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4665500/files/figure.png" .

